<!-- CSS provides several properties to style the appearance of text. These include:

font-family: Specifies the typeface (e.g., Arial, Times New Roman).
font-size: Defines the size of the text.
font-weight: Controls the thickness or boldness of the text.
text-align: Aligns text horizontally within its container.
color: Changes the text color.
line-height: Adjusts the spacing between lines of text.
text-decoration: Modifies the appearance of links (e.g., underline). -->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text and Font Styling Example</title>

    <style>
        /* Styling Headings */
        h1 {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            font-size: 36px;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
            color: darkblue;
        }

        h2 {
            font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: normal;
            text-align: left;
            color: darkgreen;
        }

        /* Styling Paragraphs */
        p {
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            text-align: justify;
            color: #333;
        }

        /* Styling Links */
        a {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            font-size: 16px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: blue;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
            color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Welcome to CSS Text Styling</h1>

    <h2>Heading 2 Example</h2>
    <p>
        This is a paragraph styled with the <code>font-family</code>, <code>font-size</code>, and
        <code>line-height</code> properties.
        The text is aligned using <code>text-align: justify</code> to ensure it is evenly distributed across the width
        of the container.
    </p>

    <p>
        The <strong>font-weight</strong> property is used to make this text bold, and the <em>font-style</em> property
        makes this text italic.
    </p>

    <a href="#">This is a styled link</a>
    <p>Hover over the link to see the effect of the <code>:hover</code> pseudo-class.</p>

</body>

</html>

<!-- Summary
This example demonstrates how to style a variety of text elements using CSS. We applied different fonts, sizes, colors, and alignment to headings, paragraphs, and links. Styling text properly can improve readability and the visual appeal of a webpage. The hover effect on the link enhances user interaction. -->